This paper deals with the design and implementation of a new write-only ORAM, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance of the ORAM on different storage devices, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB) and operating systems (cs.OS). Finally, the paper mentions plausible deniability and censorship-resilient systems, which could be related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
